a.虚伪的 【英】 adj. 虚伪的(of hypocrisy or a hypocrite) 【记】 hypocrite+cal adj. 虚伪的; 伪善的 【记】hypo下面, critical(adj 评论的; 批评的)－在背后批评的－伪善的 【参】hypocrite[SAT](n 伪君子); hypodermic(adj 皮下的n 皮下注射); epidermis(n 表皮; 上皮) 【类】authenticity: fraudulent = sincerity: hypercritical真实不是欺骗的 = 真诚不是虚伪的 【反】ingenuous(adj 坦白的; 直率的); honest(adj 诚实正直的) 【记】hypo 在下面 + criticize 批评 → 在下面批评 表面上不批评 hypocritical (adj.)  1540s (implied in hypocritically), from hypocritic, which was used in the same sense, + -al (1). Middle English used simple hypocrite as the adjective (c.1400) as well as the noun.
